Public repository for OpenFOAM development by Caelan Lapointe, Peter Hamlington, and co-authors.

Currently includes:

diffusionFireFoam solver code, updated dynamicRefineFvMesh library, and test cases.
Relevant publication: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.firesaf.2019.102934

wildFireFoam solver code for of6/7, associated custom libraries, and test cases discused in the following publication:
C. Lapointe, N.T. Wimer, J.F. Glusman, A.S. Makowiecki, J.W. Daily, G.B. Rieker, and P.E. Hamlington. Efficient Simulation of Fire Spread Using Adaptive Mesh Refinement. Combustion Theory and Modeling (submitted)

fireDyMFoam solver code for of7, associated custom libraries, and example cases.
Relevant publication: https://doi.org/10.3390/fluids6090323

adjointRhoReactingCentralFoam, for topology optimization of reacting, compresisble flows. Works with discreteAdjointOpenFOAM, developed by Towara and Naumann 
(https://doi.org/10.1016/j.procs.2013.05.206). Incorporates piso-central code of Kraposhin et. al (https://doi.org/10.1002/fld.4512, https://doi.org/10.1016/j.procs.2015.11.007).
Relevant publication: https://doi.org/10.2514/6.2017-4115

